# Applications — [ORG_SLUG]

Inventory of all software applications owned by [ORG_SLUG].

## Structure

One folder per app:
```
applications/
├── <app-1>/
│   └── README.md
├── <app-2>/
│   └── README.md
└── ...
```

## Per-app README content

Each app folder's `README.md` should contain:
- Purpose (1-2 sentences)
- Stack (Java/Node/Rust/etc.)
- Repository URL
- Production host(s)
- Owner / team
- LGPD relevance (yes/no, link to matrix row)
- Key documents in the app's own repo (architecture.md, decisions.md, etc.)

## Auto-registration

When a developer runs `/rsct-setup` in an app's repository and this universe
is detected locally, the framework offers (consent-gated) to register the app
here — it writes `applications/<app>/README.md` into this universe's working
tree for you to review and commit (RSCT never commits the universe itself).

You can always register an app by hand instead: create
`applications/<app>/README.md` from `_app.md.template`.
